            "text_block_arGWMc": {
              "type": "text-block",
              "name": "Text block",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Carat is a measure of a diamond's weight, not its size. One carat equals 200 milligrams, and each carat is divided into 100 points. While carat weight significantly influences a diamond's value, two diamonds of equal weight can appear quite different in size depending on their cut quality and proportions. A well-cut diamond with optimal proportions will appear larger than a poorly cut diamond of the same weight because it maximizes the visible surface area and reflects more light. This is why considering cut quality alongside carat weight is important for finding a diamond that looks both beautiful and substantial. When selecting a diamond, consider how it will look in its setting and on the wearer's hand. Sometimes a slightly smaller diamond with exceptional cut and clarity creates more impact than a larger stone with visible flaws or dullness.",
                "font": "--font-family-second",
